# Slash Design

Use this rule when the user asks for presentation design, HTML slides, pitch decks, visual storytelling, design taste, design critique, or converting PowerPoint content into a web presentation.

Before acting, read the local Slash skill instructions if they are present in the project:

- `.cursor/slash-skills/design/frontend-slides/SKILL.md`

Follow the referenced skill workflow. In particular:

- Keep generated slide decks as fixed 16:9 stages.
- Prefer distinctive visual systems over generic templates.
- Build real usable outputs, not advice-only summaries, when the user asks for a deck.
- Preserve the skill's supporting files next to `SKILL.md` when copying this adapter into a Cursor project.

